data.text:
JR Smith showing good conditioning

G JR Smith is showing good conditioning, and Lakers' HC Frank Vogel "raved" about having him on the Lakers.

Fantasy Impact

"His nickname is ‘Swish’ for a reason," said Vogel. "He’s a big-time shot maker and he looks like he’s in terrific physical condition." Smith signed with the Lakers on July 1st. The 34-year-old will play a key role off the Lakers' bench. JR averaged 6.7 points, 1.6 rebounds, 1.9 assists, 1.0 steals and 1.1 triples across 11 games for the Cavaliers in the 2018-19 season.
